Tim Peake: Twitter looks ahead to UK astronaut's lift-off

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Maj Tim Peake will become the first British European Space Agency (Esa) astronaut to go into space, on Tuesday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The former Army helicopter pilot and two fellow crew members will launch to the International Space Station (ISS) on a landmark flight from Baikonur Cosmodrome, in Kazakhstan.
To mark the launch, #BritinSpace, #Principia - the name of the six-month mission - and #TimPeake are all trending on Twitter.
